  "body": "rpcdaemon does not log any success or failure of correctly configuring the chaindata folder...\r\n\r\nIf I run rpcdaemon with only `--private.api.addr=\"localhost:9090\"` all is well.\r\n\r\nIf I run rpcdaemon with `--private.api.addr=\"localhost:9090\"` AND `--chaindata=\"/incorrect/path\"` all is well :-1: there is no log indicating that it failed to open the chandata path, it just does its thing.\r\n\r\nIf I run rpcdaemon with `--private.api.addr=\"localhost:9090\"` AND `--chaindata=\"/correct/path/chaindata\"` all is well :+1: but there's no log or indication that it was correctly configured or that it's operating in dual mode :-1: \r\n\r\nHopefully this make sense.\r\n\r\nI kinda feel like the `--datadir=\"/data/turbo-geth/datadir\"` flag should be consistent with the rpcdaemon flag, but as far as I can tell I need to use `--chaindata=\"/data/turbo-geth/datadir/tg/chaindata\"` which is a little more confusing.",
